    "FLORIDAS FAVORITE COLORED WEEKLY Office at 1112 NW Third Avenue Miami FloridaTelephone 32236 Plant at 6740 NW 15th AvenueTelephone 846128 Entered aa Second Claaa Matter August 9 1927 at the Post Office at Miami Florida under the act of March 3 1876 H E BIGIBMUND REEVES Editor GARTH C REEVEB Business Manager ADVERTISING REPRESENTATIVE Interstate United Newspapers Incorporated 545 Fifth Ave New York Member of the Associated Negro Press Member of the National Newspaper Publishers Association BUBB6RIPTION RATES ONE YEAR 400 BIX MONTHB 250 THREE MONTHS 150 REPUBLICAN CONVENTION Next Tuesday the Republicans hold their national convention in Chicago At this convention they will name the partys choice for president and vice president of the United States The two outstanding candidates for pres ident are Senator Robert A Taft and General Dwight D Eisenhower Both seem confident of victory The vote should be close As far as we know the Republicans platform evad ed the Civil Rights issue The CIO has called upon the Republican party to disavow the political coalition between the reactionary elements of the Republican Party and equally reactionary Democrats The statement was presented to the Platform Draft ing Committee of the Republican National Convention in Chicago"
